Oh, president of what?

54
00:02:54,570 --> 00:02:58,446
Oberoende, it's a micro nation.

55
00:02:58,470 --> 00:03:02,316
A nation within a
nation, right here in LA.

56
00:03:02,340 --> 00:03:04,416
Well like the Cherokee Nation?

57
00:03:04,440 --> 00:03:05,916
That's my nation, you know?

58
00:03:05,940 --> 00:03:08,916
We have 380,000 tribal citizens.

59
00:03:08,940 --> 00:03:10,233
How about your nation?

60
00:03:11,580 --> 00:03:15,846
Well, we had a few now and
then, and over the years,

61
00:03:15,870 --> 00:03:20,256
but now you're looking
at its sole inhabitant.

62
00:03:20,280 --> 00:03:22,386
Oh, we gotta start somewhere.

63
00:03:22,410 --> 00:03:24,966
We still have time to
get everything together.

64
00:03:24,990 --> 00:03:26,571
So you're with me?

65
00:03:26,595 --> 00:03:29,856
Yeah, I like what you have to say.

66
00:03:29,880 --> 00:03:32,856
But you have to stop
preaching on street corners.

67
00:03:32,880 --> 00:03:35,196
So you've heard of me before.

68
00:03:35,220 --> 00:03:36,270
You could say that.

69
00:03:37,680 --> 00:03:40,308
So how is the campaign gonna be funded?

70
00:03:40,332 --> 00:03:41,142
No problem.

71
00:03:41,166 --> 00:03:41,975
Oh.

72
00:03:41,999 --> 00:03:42,999
I'm so sorry.

73
00:03:52,080 --> 00:03:55,926
So you were saying, that
financing the campaign

74
00:03:55,950 --> 00:03:57,426
is not a problem?

75
00:03:57,450 --> 00:04:00,216
Are you a multimillionaire?

76
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:01,799
Do I look like one?

77
00:04:01,823 --> 00:04:04,383
No, but I just figured, it might help.

78
00:04:06,480 --> 00:04:10,623
Well, I have enough to
get by, but I'm no Trump.

79
00:04:12,420 --> 00:04:14,886
Actually, those would
donate to the campaign

80
00:04:14,910 --> 00:04:16,506
will fund the solutions to the problems

81
00:04:16,530 --> 00:04:18,246
close to their hearts.

82
00:04:18,270 --> 00:04:21,756
And when we have enough money
to solve a particular problem,

83
00:04:21,780 --> 00:04:23,430
its solution will be implemented.

84
00:04:24,810 --> 00:04:25,923
That's a good idea.

85
00:04:27,480 --> 00:04:28,480
Thanks.

86
00:04:30,720 --> 00:04:31,720
Here.

87
00:04:37,110 --> 00:04:40,206
So how are you gonna get
people to believe in you enough

88
00:04:40,230 --> 00:04:42,243
to part with their hard-earned cash?

89
00:04:43,170 --> 00:04:48,170
Oh well, if I just had
enough charisma I could do it.

90
00:04:49,860 --> 00:04:52,836
I think I may be of service.

91
00:04:52,860 --> 00:04:55,653
So my lack of sight isn't a negative?

92
00:04:56,700 --> 00:04:59,106
Well actually FDR was elected four times

93
00:04:59,130 --> 00:05:00,480
and he was in a wheelchair.

94
00:05:01,740 --> 00:05:04,533
I think your Asperger's
might be more of a problem.

95
00:05:05,460 --> 00:05:06,753
Are your doctor?

96
00:05:06,777 --> 00:05:09,906
No. No, I'm just observant.

97
00:05:09,930 --> 00:05:11,286
Huh.

98
00:05:11,310 --> 00:05:14,433
Well, would you like to visit Oberoende?

99
00:05:15,570 --> 00:05:17,103
Sure, let's go.

100
00:05:18,120 --> 00:05:19,620
My car's just on the corner,

101
00:05:20,580 --> 00:05:24,333
