that have decided to carry Smart Magic.

1347
01:06:30,750 --> 01:06:33,336
Some reports claim the
National Gun Association

1348
01:06:33,360 --> 01:06:35,346
is behind these boycotts,

1349
01:06:35,370 --> 01:06:37,473
but the NGA has officially denied it.

1350
01:06:37,497 --> 01:06:39,123
Are we ready with plan B?

1351
01:06:39,990 --> 01:06:42,936
Well, we have applications
for Smart Magic franchises,

1352
01:06:42,960 --> 01:06:45,606
for entrepreneurs across the country.

1353
01:06:45,630 --> 01:06:48,666
We're gonna have a few stores
up and running really soon.

1354
01:06:48,690 --> 01:06:51,546
We're here with Judy and Alex Robertson,

1355
01:06:51,570 --> 01:06:55,716
franchise owners of a
Smart Magic gun shop.

1356
01:06:55,740 --> 01:06:56,946
They are two survivors

1357
01:06:56,970 --> 01:07:00,813
of what is now being called
the Smart Magic Massacre.

1358
01:07:01,740 --> 01:07:03,243
What time did this take place?

1359
01:07:04,260 --> 01:07:08,616
It was about 2:00 AM, Judy
and I plus one of our employees

1360
01:07:08,640 --> 01:07:10,446
had stayed late to get everything ready

1361
01:07:10,470 --> 01:07:11,796
for today's grand opening.

1362
01:07:11,820 --> 01:07:13,916
And we had just turned the lights out

1363
01:07:13,940 --> 01:07:15,006
and we were about to head home.

1364
01:07:15,030 --> 01:07:17,886
That's when we saw like
the flickering lights

1365
01:07:17,910 --> 01:07:20,346
coming towards us
through the front window,

1366
01:07:20,370 --> 01:07:24,516
and we received several death threats.

1367
01:07:24,540 --> 01:07:28,203
So we were obviously already nervous.

1368
01:07:31,770 --> 01:07:32,796
I thought we were gonna die.

1369
01:07:32,820 --> 01:07:33,787
It's okay.

1370
01:07:33,811 --> 01:07:34,983
We're safe now, dear.

1371
01:07:36,120 --> 01:07:38,970
We've obtained security
camera footage of the incident.

1372
01:07:42,240 --> 01:07:44,196
The footage you're about
to see is pretty graphic,

1373
01:07:44,220 --> 01:07:47,223
so we must ask for viewer
discretion before watching.

1374
01:07:49,980 --> 01:07:51,246
[Alex] They approached
the front of the shop

1375
01:07:51,270 --> 01:07:54,306
so we grabbed some Smart
Magic firearms and ammo.

1376
01:07:54,330 --> 01:07:56,916
They were prepared for confrontation

1377
01:07:56,940 --> 01:07:59,916
and they were wearing body
armor, they were well armed.

1378
01:07:59,940 --> 01:08:01,086
You can see there.

1379
01:08:01,110 --> 01:08:03,576
We hit that man on the
leg with the magic bullet,

1380
01:08:03,600 --> 01:08:05,601
the guy went down in seconds.

1381
01:08:05,625 --> 01:08:07,176
(gunshots ringing)
(alarm bell ringing)

1382
01:08:07,200 --> 01:08:09,276
Our building alarm was triggered

1383
01:08:09,300 --> 01:08:11,433
and all three of us started firing back.

1384
01:08:12,475 --> 01:08:13,896
(siren wailing)

1385
01:08:13,920 --> 01:08:16,176
[Reporter] Alex is that
you saving that man's life?

1386
01:08:16,200 --> 01:08:18,396
[Alex] We could hear
the sirens approaching,

1387
01:08:18,420 --> 01:08:21,396
any of the attackers that were
still conscious had run off.

1388
01:08:21,420 --> 01:08:24,606
So I felt it was safe
that we put out the flame

1389
01:08:24,630 --> 01:08:26,430
before the guy was seriously burned.

1390
01:08:28,179 --> 01:08:30,846
(radio chatter)

1391
01:08:33,330 --> 01:08:36,606
But one question, your
attackers are wearing body armor,

1392
01:08:36,630 --> 01:08:39,153
how were you able to take them out?

1393
01:08:40,680 --> 01:08:42,666
We were just aiming for their arms,

1394
01:08:42,690 --> 01:08:44,436
their legs, their butts,

1395
01:08:44,460 --> 01:08:47,706
like any place that was
vulnerable to our ammo.

1396
01:08:47,730 --> 01:08:50,376
So none of them were
permanently injured?

1397
01:08:50,400 --> 01:08:53,283
No, we're told they're
conscious and under arrest.

1398
01:08:54,330 --> 01:08:57,276
Wow, they went down so fast.

1399
01:08:57,300 --> 01:08:58,686
We're just as surprised as you are.

1400
01:08:58,710 --> 01:09:00,966
I mean, we'd heard all about this weaponry

1401
01:09:00,990 --> 01:09:03,186
when we decided to open
a Smart Magic franchise,

1402
01:09:03,210 --> 01:09:06,936
but we never expected
it to be this effective.

1403
01:09:06,960 --> 01:09:09,846
And if it wasn't, we'd be dead.

1404
01:09:09,870 --> 01:09:13,116
Other reports from Smart Magic
locations throughout the US

1405
01:09:13,140 --> 01:09:14,973
show sales skyrocketing.

1406
01:09:16,140 --> 01:09:18,726
Several major cities across the US

1407
01:09:18,750 --> 01:09:20,196
have asked to test the weapons

1408
01:09:20,220 --> 01:09:22,986
for their city's police departments.

1409
01:09:23,010 --> 01:09:26,106
Even the leaders of the
National Gun Association,

1410
01:09:26,130 --> 01:09:28,176
who were originally skeptical,

1411
01:09:28,200 --> 01:09:31,426
have asked to meet with
presidential candidate, Patrick Lee.

1412
01:09:31,450 --> 01:09:33,950
(all applaud)

1413
01:09:35,785 --> 01:09:38,376
We have had a long and
fruitful discussion with Mr. Lee

1414
01:09:38,400 --> 01:09:39,756
and Miss Seedlingsun,

1415
01:09:39,780 --> 01:09:42,396
along with members of
the gun control lobby.

1416
01:09:42,420 --> 01:09:44,286
We have come to the conclusion
that we are in support

1417
01:09:44,310 --> 01:09:46,510
of this new solution
to the gun controversy.

1418
01:09:47,370 --> 01:09:48,996
While we originally thought Smart Magic

1419
01:09:49,020 --> 01:09:50,916
would give a false sense of security

1420
01:09:50,940 --> 01:09:52,566
to those who wanted to protect themselves

1421
01:09:52,590 --> 01:09:53,736
and their families,

1422
01:09:53,760 --> 01:09:55,506
we now accept that it has been proven

1423
01:09:55,530 --> 01:09:57,936
to be a viable weapon system.

1424
01:09:57,960 --> 01:10:02,256
So much so that the NGA is
joining the gun control lobby

1425
01:10:02,280 --> 01:10:05,016
to back Patrick Lee's run for president

1426
01:10:05,040 --> 01:10:06,243
of the United States.

1427
01:10:07,230 --> 01:10:10,026
Presidential Dark Horse Patrick Lee

1428
01:10:10,050 --> 01:10:12,006
stopped by the White House this afternoon

1429
01:10:12,030 --> 01:10:14,673
after having a very successful
meeting with the NGA.

1430
01:10:15,750 --> 01:10:18,546
Now it has been confirmed
that he is up 15%

1431
01:10:18,570 --> 01:10:19,896
in the national polls

1432
01:10:19,920 --> 01:10:22,866
and has also been invited
to join democratic

1433
01:10:22,890 --> 01:10:26,316
and Republican nominees for
the first presidential debate.

1434
01:10:26,340 --> 01:10:28,836
Now this should make
for a very interesting

1435
01:10:28,860 --> 01:10:30,246
and amazing opportunity

1436
01:10:30,270 --> 01:10:33,246
to see him in the presidential debate.

1437
01:10:33,270 --> 01:10:35,946
And now onto international news.

1438
01:10:35,970 --> 01:10:38,856
The border dispute
between India and Pakistan

1439
01:10:38,880 --> 01:10:40,626
continues to escalate,

1440
01:10:40,650 --> 01:10:43,713
which causes more
concern around the world.

1441
01:10:44,713 --> 01:10:47,130
(calm music)

1442
01:11:02,876 --> 01:11:05,876
(keyboard clatters)

1443
01:11:10,050 --> 01:11:11,300
What are those figures?

1444
01:11:12,990 --> 01:11:14,796
Have you been working
on this the entire time

1445
01:11:14,820 --> 01:11:16,773
instead of rehearsing for the debate?

1446
01:11:17,790 --> 01:11:22,356
Well, I think I just
solved another problem.

1447
01:11:22,380 --> 01:11:23,733
Oh, what?

1448
01:11:24,720 --> 01:11:27,063
I discovered how to
eliminate national debt.

1449
01:11:28,260 --> 01:11:29,946
Are you kidding?

1450
01:11:29,970 --> 01:11:33,003
You think I spent all that
time just for the fun of it?

1451
01:11:33,960 --> 01:11:36,963
Oh, my neck is killing me.

1452
01:11:41,190 --> 01:11:42,606
Well, I've actually been spending

1453
01:11:42,630 --> 01:11:43,926
a lot of time planning this,

1454
01:11:43,950 --> 01:11:46,683
but the missing part of the
solution just came to me.

1455
01:11:47,580 --> 01:11:49,116
Wait, so that's a formula

1456
01:11:49,140 --> 01:11:51,183
for eliminating the national debt?

1457
01:11:52,050 --> 01:11:54,336
Yeah, by cryptocurrency.

1458
01:11:54,360 --> 01:11:58,056
I mean, it's not like E equals
MC squared, but it'll work.

1459
01:11:58,080 --> 01:11:59,047
Wow, okay.

1460
01:11:59,071 --> 01:12:01,720
This is gonna really give
us a hand up in the debate.

1461
01:12:02,670 --> 01:12:05,020
Oh, I can't use this
for the debate actually.

1462
01:12:06,330 --> 01:12:07,356
Why not?

1463
01:12:07,380 --> 01:12:08,946
Well, because I have to implement it

1464
01:12:08,970 --> 01:12:11,171
when I'm in the White House.

1465
01:12:11,195 --> 01:12:13,116
So?

1466
01:12:13,140 --> 01:12:13,957
Did you forget?

1467
01:12:13,981 --> 01:12:17,646
We made a promise not
to make any promises.

1468
01:12:17,670 --> 01:12:19,733
Okay, but this could
really put us ahead.

1469
01:12:19,757 --> 01:12:22,596
No, we have to keep this under wraps.

1470
01:12:22,620 --> 01:12:24,783
I can't believe I
didn't see this coming.

1471
01:12:27,240 --> 01:12:30,666
Is there anything else
you've been keeping from me?

1472
01:12:30,690 --> 01:12:35,433
Well, I have a plan for
eliminating federal income tax.

1473
01:12:36,390 --> 01:12:38,253
Can we use that in a debate?

1474
01:12:39,090 --> 01:12:40,143
No.

1475
01:12:41,220 --> 01:12:42,576
What are we even training for

1476
01:12:42,600 --> 01:12:45,126
if we can't use all of your ammunition?

1477
01:12:45,150 --> 01:12:48,156
Well, we can use whatever
we've already accomplished.

1478
01:12:48,180 --> 01:12:51,063
Okay, but if we win, we can use it then?

1479
01:12:52,302 --> 01:12:55,593
Yeah, but we still need the
Congress to go along with it.

1480
01:12:56,853 --> 01:12:57,663
Okay.

1481
01:12:57,687 --> 01:12:58,896
(enchanting music)

1482
01:12:58,920 --> 01:13:03,663
I'll figure out how to say it
without making any promises.

1483
01:13:04,980 --> 01:13:06,546
Your hair is getting too long,

1484
01:13:06,570 --> 01:13:08,616
we have to cut it before the debate.

1485
01:13:08,640 --> 01:13:10,086
Don't wait up for me.

1486
01:13:10,110 --> 01:13:12,696
I've got a presentation
with some top educators

1487
01:13:12,720 --> 01:13:15,036
about our new way of running
the nations' schools.

1488
01:13:15,060 --> 01:13:16,686
Wish me luck.

1489
01:13:16,710 --> 01:13:18,936
Well, with your powers of persuasion,

1490
01:13:18,960 --> 01:13:20,313
you don't need any luck.

1491
01:13:24,030 --> 01:13:25,986
No more playing with numbers.

1492
01:13:26,010 --> 01:13:27,366
Focus on the campaign

1493
01:13:27,390 --> 01:13:30,273
and memorize those talking points.

1494
01:13:38,430 --> 01:13:39,911
(keyboard clatters)

1495
01:13:39,935 --> 01:13:42,352
(calm music)

1496
01:14:06,427 --> 01:14:09,177
(dramatic music)

1497
01:14:15,731 --> 01:14:18,814
("Oberoende Anthem")

1498
01:14:20,331 --> 01:14:21,331
Who is it?

1499
01:14:23,298 --> 01:14:25,356
(knocking on door)

1500
01:14:25,380 --> 01:14:26,826
Back already?

1501
01:14:26,850 --> 01:14:28,233
Did you lose your key card?

1502
01:14:31,099 --> 01:14:32,706
(enchanting music)

1503
01:14:32,730 --> 01:14:35,706
Barb, what are you doing here?

1504
01:14:35,730 --> 01:14:36,730
I wanna talk.

1505
01:14:37,583 --> 01:14:38,583
About what?

1506
01:14:40,050 --> 01:14:41,050
Let me in.

1507
01:14:42,870 --> 01:14:44,620
I don't think that's a good idea.

1508
01:14:46,980 --> 01:14:48,230
What would you suggest?

1509
01:14:51,182 --> 01:14:53,166
Why?

1510
01:14:53,190 --> 01:14:54,243
After all this time.

1511
01:14:57,780 --> 01:14:58,780
I miss you.

1512
01:15:00,510 --> 01:15:01,863
You really hurt me.

1513
01:15:04,440 --> 01:15:06,933
You still love me, don't you?

1514
01:15:08,308 --> 01:15:13,210
Of course I do, you're the
one who broke up with me.

1515
01:15:16,080 --> 01:15:17,080
I changed my mind.

1516
01:15:20,537 --> 01:15:24,403
I've been calling you, but
you refuse to talk to me.

1517
01:15:27,342 --> 01:15:30,243
I've been a little tied up.

1518
01:15:30,267 --> 01:15:32,043
You always used to say you loved me,

1519
01:15:32,067 --> 01:15:33,753
but you never had time for me.

1520
01:15:37,230 --> 01:15:41,136
I'm sorry, I was busy with my clients,

1521
01:15:41,160 --> 01:15:42,393
growing the business.

1522
01:15:43,440 --> 01:15:47,283
Yeah, just like you're
busy with your campaign.

1523
01:15:49,620 --> 01:15:51,920
We haven't seen each
other in all this time.

1524
01:15:52,770 --> 01:15:53,853
What changed?

1525
01:15:55,650 --> 01:15:58,143
I'm older now, more mature.

1526
01:15:59,940 --> 01:16:01,790
I think we could really make it work.

1527
01:16:03,596 --> 01:16:06,013
(calm music)

1528
01:16:11,820 --> 01:16:13,720
We had some really good times up here.

1529
01:16:16,170 --> 01:16:17,440
Remember that one time

1530
01:16:18,330 --> 01:16:21,753
where you and I were fooling around naked,

1531
01:16:23,490 --> 01:16:25,203
and that helicopter flew over?

1532
01:16:31,129 --> 01:16:34,326
You know, we could try it again.

1533
01:16:34,350 --> 01:16:35,350
Now that it's dark.

1534
01:16:39,330 --> 01:16:40,850
I really don't know.

1535
01:16:42,120 --> 01:16:43,520
I have a whole new life now.

1536
01:16:44,679 --> 01:16:47,733
I know, I miss you.

1537
01:16:50,182 --> 01:16:52,083
We were meant to be together.

1538
01:16:54,570 --> 01:16:55,570
I know that now.

1539
01:16:57,810 --> 01:16:59,913
If I felt that you really meant that.

1540
01:17:02,820 --> 01:17:07,820
I still love you, but
you broke up with me,

1541
01:17:08,427 --> 01:17:10,503
and when I really needed you the most.

1542
01:17:12,840 --> 01:17:17,493
I was losing my sight
and the belief in myself,

1543
01:17:19,309 --> 01:17:20,793
and you just made it worse.

1544
01:17:22,890 --> 01:17:24,726
I'll make it up to you.

1545
01:17:24,750 --> 01:17:26,106
I promise, Pat.

1546
01:17:26,130 --> 01:17:28,743
Please, just give me a chance.

1547
01:17:31,472 --> 01:17:33,889
(calm music)

1548
01:17:35,550 --> 01:17:39,123
Wait, you're not doing this
for your citizenship, are you?

1549
01:17:40,970 --> 01:17:41,970
No.

1550
01:17:42,814 --> 01:17:44,164
No, I've got my green card.

1551
01:17:46,920 --> 01:17:48,020
We could tie the knot,

1552
01:17:49,597 --> 01:17:51,740
we could make this official.

1553
01:17:51,764 --> 01:17:53,432
I have to think about this.

1554
01:17:53,456 --> 01:17:54,956
No, don't think.

1555
01:17:56,017 --> 01:18:00,963
We could make this work
with me as your wife.

1556
01:18:02,070 --> 01:18:04,953
I get it, you really think I can win.

1557
01:18:06,270 --> 01:18:10,593
Yes, with me by your side.

1558
01:18:12,266 --> 01:18:15,393
You don't love me,
you wanna be first lady.

1559
01:18:18,270 --> 01:18:20,883
Yes, but I also love you.

1560
01:18:22,110 --> 01:18:23,913
We make the perfect team.

1561
01:18:24,810 --> 01:18:27,993
Your brains, my beauty.

1562
01:18:29,250 --> 01:18:31,750
I may be blind, but I
can see right through you.

1563
01:18:33,750 --> 01:18:36,100
We've been together way
too long for me not to.

1564
01:18:37,980 --> 01:18:39,469
What are you saying?

1565
01:18:39,493 --> 01:18:41,013
I'm saying we're through,

1566
01:18:41,850 --> 01:18:43,900
like what you said when you broke it off.

1567
01:18:46,980 --> 01:18:48,336
You son of a bitch!

1568
01:18:48,360 --> 01:18:50,316
No cussing, please.

1569
01:18:50,340 --> 01:18:52,296
You think you're so powerful

1570
01:18:52,320 --> 01:18:53,796
now that you're gonna debate the big guys?

1571
01:18:53,820 --> 01:18:56,706
Well, I'm not so helpless
that I can't bring you down.

1572
01:18:56,730 --> 01:18:59,886
Well fine, go ahead and try.

1573
01:18:59,910 --> 01:19:01,116
I don't care.

1574
01:19:01,140 --> 01:19:04,296
You forget, I worked
with you in the office.

1575
01:19:04,320 --> 01:19:06,186
I know all of your secrets.

1576
01:19:06,210 --> 01:19:07,710
Well, you got nothing on me.

1577
01:19:10,620 --> 01:19:13,116
You think you have the upper hand?

1578
01:19:13,140 --> 01:19:15,963
Yes, I think I finally do.

1579
01:19:17,850 --> 01:19:19,053
We'll see about that.

1580
01:19:27,750 --> 01:19:29,046
You'll miss me when I'm gone.

1581
01:19:29,070 --> 01:19:30,486
No, I won't.

1582
01:19:30,510 --> 01:19:31,536
And ever since you left,

1583
01:19:31,560 --> 01:19:34,527
I learned how to stand on my own two feet.

1584
01:19:37,432 --> 01:19:40,146
(Patrick groans)

1585
01:19:40,170 --> 01:19:41,253
I can see that.

1586
01:19:45,570 --> 01:19:47,103
Goodbye, Mr. President.

1587
01:19:53,730 --> 01:19:55,053
He's all yours bitch!

1588
01:20:03,030 --> 01:20:04,030
I'm waiting.

1589
01:20:05,215 --> 01:20:06,215
Oh gosh.

1590
01:20:08,093 --> 01:20:09,093
That was Barb.

1591
01:20:10,020 --> 01:20:11,020
Who?

1592
01:20:12,420 --> 01:20:16,326
My ex-girlfriend, she
wanted to get back together.

1593
01:20:16,350 --> 01:20:17,676
Ow.

1594
01:20:17,700 --> 01:20:20,406
Well you two did a fine job.

1595
01:20:20,430 --> 01:20:22,773
I can't believe I didn't foresee this.

1596
01:20:25,590 --> 01:20:27,003
Ow, my good leg!

1597
01:20:36,390 --> 01:20:38,313
Barb and I are over, we're finished.

1598
01:20:42,000 --> 01:20:45,213
You never told me about her, why?

1599
01:20:46,440 --> 01:20:48,213
She's young and attractive,

1600
01:20:49,894 --> 01:20:52,811
I just didn't want you to be upset.

1601
01:20:54,660 --> 01:20:57,473
I don't wanna lose you.

1602
01:20:57,497 --> 01:21:00,426
But we don't have that
kind of relationship,

1603
01:21:00,450 --> 01:21:01,776
it's only business.

